,Recommended,233290,33758856,Posted: 23 July,all,Screen 7,"A good game with a nice story that is set in an interesting location. A smooth blend of LA Noire, Dishonored and Arkham Asylum like gameplay mechanics with a kind of John Marston lead character, that all mix very well to create a compelling and quite unique action-adventure that you could almost call ""Ghost"" The Game.Maybe a little short, or maybe just right if you're looking for a game to play and complete in a single session. Maybe a little pricey, but well worth it on discount. Plenty for completionists to get stuck into. The end is a little abrupt but hard to tell if it was a sly cliffhanger or not, regardless I would certainly play a follow-up whether this character's story is over or not.Thanks for a ""dead"" good time and an interesting investigation!"
,Recommended,233290,33141053,Posted: 2 July,all,Lady Sekhmet,"I know there are some negatives reviews around here, (and some of them are fair enough) but I wanted to give this game a try.I won't go into details about the story because it really is catchy, at least to me. The concept of mixing investigations and detective skills with paranormal stuff is great, even though you're not even ""deducing"" anything because the game is quite straightfoward in that aspect. It almost tells you what to choose (and even if you chose the wrong answer, the game would give you infinite opportunities until you get the right one.) It'd have been great to change the story if you failed, but... well.The setting and visuals are awesome. I really liked where the story takes place. Funny thing is that I read The Crucible a few weeks ago, and I read the name Salem hundreds of times. I started playing this game and BOOM! Salem again! Puritans and witch trials, yay! This helps to create a great atmosphere.Speaking of enemies, you don't actually face any real danger during the gameplay. There are some demons, which are easily avoidable, and you can even disable them so they won't attack you. I don't recommend this because they are in fact so easy to kill. and it's not that there are too many, so...Long story short, I'd recommend this game (you can even possess cats!) but I don't think it's quite fair to pay its full price. Get it on sale!"
