76561198216317917,Recommended,233290,34690474,Posted: 2 September,all,ArtChimera,"I do recommend this game, with some reservations.The premise was really interesting, and the visuals and voice acting were great. Where it fell flattest for me were the ""investigations."" I normally hate using quotations for emphasis, but it's really warranted in this case. They were so laughably straight forward and simple that I actually tripped myself up the first two questions, because I thought there was no way it would be so obvious. If you're expecting something more in depth a la LA Noire you'll be disappointed. It quickly became evident that the investigations were there just to push you from plot point to plot point, no critical thinking need apply. I had seen that in other people's reviews and they're spot on.There aren't that many side quests either- I had thought there would be more investigations into the cases of people in the afterlife. There are four, and again those are really simple. The other side quests are basically collection quests. I don't mind a game that focuses more on character or plot, but it would be nice to have solid investigative gameplay to round it out, particularly for a game that seems to market itself that way.It just feels really unbalanced - the casual gamer appeal of simple puzzles combined with the dark supernatural detective theme feels like they're playing to two separate audiences at the same time.That said, I definitely thought it was worth picking up and playing if you enjoy these genres. Just don't expect too much out of the gameplay, and get it on a good sale."
