,Recommended,233290,14577518,"Posted: 21 February, 2015",all,Rogue,"Interesting and engaging adventure game.  Gameplay is 95% walking around finding hidden clues and talking to people.  The other 5% are quicktime events to defeat demons which are quite easy (and you can avoid some of them if you want).  I enjoyed the game's premise of trying to solve your own murder as a ghost.  The story is good - not great - but good.  Your character is likable, the dialog is reasonably well written, and the locations and plot points are well realized.  I enjoy hunting down hidden items in games, and this game offers that in plenty.  Most are reasonably easy to achieve, and some are quite cleverly hidden.  One set of collectibles though, the ghost girl drawings, are very difficult because you do not see them in the environment - you have to walk close to the walls and a ""reveal"" prompt will pop up if there is one there.If you like adventure games and murder mysteries I think you will enjoy this game.  Best of all, it does not overstay its welcome.  Steam says I completed the game in 12 hours and I was quite slow and deliberate in playing (trying to find all the collectables)."
