,Recommended,233290,10353240,"Posted: 5 June, 2014",all,Fsyco,"If L.A. Noire was like a big budget, 3D version of Ace Attorney, then this is sort of like a big budget, 3D version of Ghost Trick (which was made by the same people as Ace Attorney). Also pardon the pun, but this does feel a bit like a 'spiritual successor' to L.A. Noire, except with the focus mostly on the investigating, and some action-ish segments. Basically, if you like any of the other three games I mentioned above, you'll probably like this.It is a little on the short and easy side, but that just means that no frustrating gameplay gets in the way of the player ploughing through the plot. The writing is a little predictable, and I managed to call most of the major plot developments within the first hour, but I still wanted to know what happened next, and to be fair I was wrong about a few things. The investigating of crime scenes is pretty fun and easy, and there's also some stealth sections where you have to sneak about excorcising some genuinely creepy demons.There's also collectable story bits, like the thoughts of Ronan's wife or newspaper articles about the killer. In addition, each level and the over world has a unique set of collectable items (or rather, the same item you have to scavenge for 8-19 times) that, when all collected, get you a little narraration of a ghost story. Fair Warning: some of those are an absolute ♥♥♥♥♥ to find if you want to 100% them."
