76561197993357150,Recommended,233290,25962516,"Posted: 10 October, 2016",all,Chill,"Spoiler Alert: The main character dies. The good news is that it happens right at the start of the game. Then the game gets going. However, unlike some God of War clone this isn't a revenge fueled bloodbath of carnage and destruction. There isn't an ocean of ""enjoy to destroy"" cannon fodder to kill/loot on the way to the final boss. This is a supernatural redemption story in the vein of Ghost or Always with a dash of The Frighteners thrown in for a bit of fun.The bulk of the game will be exploring mutliple crime scenes as you piece together not only the reason for your own murder, but the deaths of many fellow spirits that you encounter along your main quest. In some regards I am reminded of the forensic analyst role from Heavy Rain. Once you have gathered enough clues in the crime scenes you can attempt to discern the next location that your journey takes you. The good news is that, unlike Heavy Rain, this game does not rely on timing based quicktime events to tell the story.However, the only real combat in the game does rely on a tried and true quicktime mechanic. This involves sneaking up behind the occasional demon and performing a stealth kill sequence to banish it. This involves a random quicktime sequence where you a flashed a direction to press along with an appropriate button/key. Not that deep.TL;DR version: If you are a casual gamer that isn't looking to mindlessly button mash your way through a plotless demon horde this is a nice change of pace. If you want some thing procedural like the Kings Quest, Monkey Island or Quantic Dream created games (Indigo Prophecy, Heavy Rain, Beyond) then you'll enjoy the storytelling. It would really fit in nicely with that friend that owns all the Telltale Games titles. Just don't expect a lot of white knuckle fragging."
76561198022820771,Not Recommended,233290,13014224,"Posted: 20 November, 2014",all,SocioPsycho,"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dtu37YI0oGU&list=UU7_-PLIhjsEBwIQXqKxmNpAMurdered: Soul Suspect is a console port detective game with a horroratmosphere that plays more like an interactive movie than a game.  Right offthe bat, I was unimpressed by the whopping 30 frames per second that thisgame runs at, followed shortly by the delayed lineup of subtitles to speech.The story was cheesy and doesn't fit with the objective of the game;starting out by stating that your ultimate goal is to reunite with a lost love,but then not mentioning that relationship for the bulk of the game.  As for the gamebeing a detective game, I would disagree with that and state that it is morelike a hidden object game that requires you search out 'clues' in a predeterminedlocation.  There is no deduction needed; all the clues are in one place, andthe game holds your hand by leading you to the next clue and askingrediculously obvious questions.The ghosts, while contributing to the atmosphere, did absolutely nothingto add to the game.  For the most part, they were all from the same time period,and were supposed to add a spooky element, but as you are also playing as aghost, and they disappear when you get close, they were more of a waste of timethan anything else.I enjoy watching movies, but I buy games in order to, oh I don't know,play a game!  This game played like a cinematic movie, with about 20-25%of the game actual gameplay, and the rest being cinematic movies or dialogue.Being made to move all across the mapp to get to the next action point does notcount as gameplay;  it is wasting time.If you are interested in the story of this game, I would recommend goingto YouTube and watching the cinematics strung together rather than buy this game.It treats you, the player, as if you are an idiot that can't figure out anythingfor yourself.  Graphically the game gets by, as well as the level design.  Thestory is acceptable, but what little gameplay there is designed for thosethat can't deduce anything for themselves.  As a game, I cannot recommend this,if it can even be called a game.For more details, see the linked video review, as this is a basic summary ofwhat I cover in my video.Thanks for your viewership and support for more videos check click here.http://www.youtube.com/user/SocioPyscho"
