,Recommended,233290,34895066,Posted: 11 September,all,EbonHawk,"It's been out awhile, and yes it has a few minor problems still, but the game is a cinematic masterpiece filled with creepy atmosphere and on-edge moments of spooky little girls and creepy creatures and unsettling moods.The ending is a bit disjointed, bland, and unfulfilling, but the game makes up for it in the journey to get there. Lots of sleuthing and clue-finding along the way keep you occupied for the 8 to 10 hours it will take you to finish this game.Ronan has been murdered (gasp! spoiler, but you knew that already) and he has to piece together what has happened and why he has been caught up in this past-meets-present mish-mash of mayhem in creepy ol' Salem, Mass.  The streets are filled with spooky ghostly spectres, and you're constantly tasked with finding the next clue to what happened to you. You also have to solve the case of the Bell Killer, as well, and find some missing persons. As sidequests, you have to help the dearly departed gain some closure and help them move on in the afterlife. You're part medium, part detective, and part ghost... live a little!It's worth fighting the slightly wonky controls to get clues to appear, and there's very little combat (except for some frequent quick-time-events later in the game; there is also an .ini hack to prevent those from becoming tedious).Very good game: the story (except for the ending) is interesting, the atmosphere is loads of creepiness, and there is way more sleuthing than slashing. Get it on sale and you won't be disappointed."
