76561198142184075,Recommended,233290,20737634,"Posted: 24 January, 2016",all,RAF3,"I have very mixed feelings about this game.  Over all I'd recommend it.  Here are my thoughts:Positives:The story was absolutely awesome.  The whole concept of solving your own death on its own was great, but then the actual mystery behind your murder is rather compelling.  I played this with my girlfriend watching and she was never ready for me to stop for the night.  So I'd recommend the game just for the story alone!Throughout the game, there are collectable items that give some insight into the history of Salem and the Witch Trials as well as random little stories about certain events relevant to the area being explored.  These add a cool dimension to the game taking away from the story and adding some cool information.Playing as a ghost and getting to use ghost abilities was pretty sweet.Negatives:The BIGGEST flaw in my opinion is the use of demons in this game.  I think the game is good enough on its own to just be a mystery without the demons in there to give a ""horror"" feel.  Truthfully, the demons didn't seem to serve a real purpose to the game and were only in a few spots to take up your time and add just a bit of difficulty to the game.  In such a story-driven game, I think leaving this out would have made the game even better because you wouldn't have to go through buildings wondering if a demon is going to pop out or not; you could have just gone on wondering about the story and exploring every facet of the city.Another big flaw, as I've read in several other reviews and agree with, is that you get really awesome ghost abilities, position, for example.  When possessing a person, you can do several things.  However, you can really only do something cool or useful with possession on major characters; on background characters, you can only mindread and for a vast majority of these characters, their thoughts are recycled (so you get the same thought from several characters throughout the city).Overall, I'd absolutely recommend this game.  While there were a couple things that bothered me, the story really was enjoyable.  Honestly, this could even make a movie.  Definitely worth a play-through."
