76561198067387196,Recommended,233290,33570595,Posted: 15 July,all,lcystratton,"I really enjoyed this game, though with a big caveat.The combat system is terrible. I became so frustrated with it that I looked up how to disable the demons' awareness in the game's files. I recommend this to all players who, like me, are playing this for the characters and story and not for the once-in-a-blue-moon exorcism.WIth that out of the way...Character. I thought the two main characers, Ronan and Joy, had a lot of personality. I loved their banter and teamwork. I wasn't really expected Ronan to be as memorable a protagonist as he was. Thanks to the bits of lore you find throughout the game, you learn a lot about Ronan's backstory and his relationship with his dead girlfriend, Julia. Usually, games that pull the dead girlfriend card don't bother to dive into what their relationship was actually like before she was fridged. It made Ronan and his motivations feel more real.Worldbuilding. There are a lot of collectibles in this game, but they all serve to flesh out the character backstories and Salem's history. I really enjoyed collecting all the tidbits of information so I could context on the town. The ghost stories were all super spooky, and I wish I had the foresight to complete them all. All of the NPCs have unique dialogue you can hear when you read their minds, which i thought was a cool touch.Also, this game is just overflowing with atmosphere. Definitley one to play with the lights off on a spooky night.Plot. I love mysteries in every medium. While I picked up on some narrative hints long before the protagonist it, the twist at the end made me gasp. I thought it was really well done. The different portions of the game were also really unique. Even when returning to a place I'd been before, I never felt like I was doing the same thing all over again.Mechanics: As I mentioned before, the quicktime events the game uses for combat were frustrating, especially since combat isn't even the primary goal of the game. However, the investigative and interactive mechanics were really fun. I thought the ways Ronan could find new information, even as a ghost, were really inspired and unique.Graphics: The cutscenes were really good. They don't get too gory, but there are some disturbing scenes as you see some really messed up murders take place.I do recommend this game to players that want to play an atmospheric, creepy, supernatural murder mystery. Just do yourself a favor and tweak the files so the demons don't frustrate you."
