,Recommended,233290,33480595,Posted: 12 July,all,Dude13,"First, because I need to get it out of the way: This game is AWESOME!! Anyway, on with the review...Dude13's MURDERED: SOUL SUSPECT review:MURDERED: SOUL SUSPECT is the story of a criminal turned cop named Ronan solving his own murder. The game takes place in Salem, Massachusetts, USA.Ronan is killed at the beginning of the game by a serial killer who has been terrorizing the town. The moniker this killer goes by is the ""Bell killer"". You spend the rest of the game tracking him down. The games is really fun, and makes you think in certain places. The characters will sometimes make you laugh out loud, but they never say anything super unimersive. Story wise, the game is really good and I always found myself wanting to go do that one side-quest or to finish this story mission - and then immediately feeling the same about the next side-quest or story mission... I wanted to experience the story.Performance wise, the game is also really good, running at 23 FPS on a computer that should NOT be able to handle this game. I have a moldy potato laptop (It doesn't even deserve the moniker microwave) from 2011 with integrated graphics processing (No GPU) and the game is playable (With a few lag spikes every once in awhile).In the voice acting and general ""feel"" departments, the game is also really good. There wasn't really had any times were the voices felt out of place or badly recorded. As to the general atmosphere and ""feel"" of the game, this is another place where the game shines. The town FEELS like a town that has been scared S***less of a serial killer. And aside from having all of the Cops playing Deus Ex while their working (Jeez Square Enix, you just couldn't resist could you), they feel nervous, scared and angry that this is all happening right under their noses - and they are especially scared now that one of their own has been killed (Ronan is a cop, remember).I REALLY like this game, but I do have a few complaints, the biggest one being the demons. The developers but in an 'enemy' creature called a Demon (And they DO look pretty demonic), and I think these demons ruin the game. I like challenging games - A LOT - but the Demons are ridiculous. The game gives you no weapons and the ONLY way to kill a Demon is to sneak up behind it and press a random combination of buttons to kill it. I wouldn't have a problem with this, except that the Demons can track you down REALLY easily (It's like they have homing beacons) and once they see you, it's basically impossible to get past the area as the demons will swarm you and kill you. The solution is to change a setting in the AI coding so that they ignore you(Instructions at the bottom under the TL; DR).The other complaint is that you can't change the key bindings - at all. The default control scheme isn't BAD per se, but I think it could be done better, and I would have REALLY liked being able to rebind the keys to what I wanted.Pros:+Story+Gameplay+Optimization+Game atmosphere+Voice acting+Level design/investigations+Also, you get to control cats... And it's even better than it soundsCons:-Demons (There is an easy fix for this tho)-You can't rebind the keys (And the default controls could be better)TL; DR:Get this game!!! I got it on a pretty steep sale, but I don't think I would have regretted getting it for its full price. If this game is on sale, GET IT!!! You will be doing yourself a disservice if you don't. This is a great game.How to make the annoying demons not bother you:1) Navigate to the folder (in your Steam folder) Murdered Soul Suspect/FateGame/Config2) Using Notepad, open the file: DefaultAIPerceptionData.ini3) Find the line:StimTypes=(TypeName=Player,BaseTypeName=Ghost,Result_Awareness=High)4) Change the ""High"" to ""Unaware"" (WITH THE ""U"" CAPITALIZED!!!! THIS IS IMPORTANT)5) Save the file, and run the gameThe demons will ignore you now. You can walk past them or kill them as many times as you want, and they won't fight back."
