76561197968907104,Not Recommended,233290,31581456,Posted: 6 May,all,TheSHEEEP,"tl;dr: Good movie, horrible game. Buy under 10$ and use cheats to skip the ""enemies"".This product has a good story (also the side-stories you discover), good atmosphere, characters and voice acting.If it was a movie, it would be pretty good. This is why ratings here are relatively high - people are pretty bad at applying standards to reviews.However, as this claims to be a games, it has to be judged as such. And it fails in almost every aspect:- First of all, there is little to no gameplay to begin with. What you actually do as a player is about as much as you do in the Telltale interactive movies (no, they are NOT games).Just much, much worse.- There is one type of ""enemy"" in this game. Not even reskins. Really just one. From beginning to end. To ""defeat"" it, you have to do a quicktime event (a random combo of 2 buttons, wow). That's it. Utterly horrible.- The ""puzzles"" in this game cannot be called such, a 5 year old could figure everything out. Yet this is clearly a game meant for an adult audience.- The controls work... barely. And sometimes they bug out. Especially the teleporting is unreliable and completely inconsistent.- Only one other ""challenge"" is finding items in each level. Really. Finding items in a level in... when did this game come out? 2014? Oh, my. So creative. And finding the last few items is a horrible nightmare as some of them are simply hidden pretty well. So - if you'd actually want to catch them all - you'd be running back and forth in the same level, checking each corner 3 times. This is game design from hell.- Replayability does not exist. There are no choices here, not even fake ones as in the Telltale products.I could go on, but you probably get the picture.Every single attempt at gameplay this game makes just falls flat or is downright offensively obnoxious.If they had stripped all the horrible ""gameplay"" elements and just made it the interactive movie they were clearly going for, the ratings for this game would have been higher.It is no wonder the devs got axed only few months after the game's release. I hope that the artists, sound people and writers got good new jobs - and that whoever was responsible for that ""gameplay"" did not get a job in the same position again. Some people are not cut to make game design."
