,Recommended,233290,23845111,"Posted: 26 June, 2016",all,"AJ, Lord of Chaos","-If you really like crime and ghosts get it on a sale-Best feature up front: you can control cats. With that out of the way: this is a detective adventure where you play as a ghost, nothing as fleshed out as Gabriel Knight, think Fahrenheit meets CSI, simplified.Graphics are not that much to look at, music the same. Voice acting and characters are good.I'm half-in so there might still be a nice surprise story-wise but it is: get clues to next location, go there, repeat.There are several logical flaws like every log shelter counting as a consecrated building you can't pass but I tolerate that.Worse are the useless collectable item hunts to add artificial length and distract from the story where you should hunt a terrible serial killer.Strange design choices like the game world's small hub being filled with collectibles every metre and questing ghosts. They'd better made several small locations accesible by quick travel like most adventures handle it.Game features no real jump scares and only moderate horror. Has quick-time-events for ""fighting"".The detective part of the game isn't actually that much brainy also and involves some guessing.Only get this if you like crime and ghost adventures very much and it's on sale. The simple clue clicking and the drive to find out about the killer sees you through.Barely recommended.Edit: finished, ending was ok, some entertainment but can be skipped with nothing missed."
