,Recommended,233290,33221101,Posted: 4 July,all,kgptzac,"Murdered: Soul Suspect, at its core, is a narrative investigation/detective game.  The twist is that the protagonist—the detective—is dead, and tries to solve his own murder, among others, as a ghost.  The story sets place in modern day Salem, Massachusetts, mixed with local mythology dating back to colonial American times… yep, the witches.Overall, the story and plot are good for a game that can easily pick up sub $10.  The QTE component of the gameplay can get annoying, especially at the finale, though.  Being a console port of 2014, this game looks very nice as of today, albeit a bit of tweaking in NVidia settings are needed.  But compare to other console ports, this one is doing more than OK, and that’s coming from me, being allergic to bad console ports.It spent me 8 hours to complete the game.  One probably can squeeze the play time under 6 hours if ignoring collectible, due to the reward is basically a little side story easily looked up on YouTube.  Side investigations are good though; not recommending to skip those.  I think Murdered: Soul Suspect should appeal to all detective game fans."
