76561198055410225,Not Recommended,233290,13626966,"Posted: 26 December, 2014",all,スパイダーマン,"Pretty average game. The core mechanic consists of searching around for objects, something similar to most collecting sidequests in modern games, which becomes boring very fast. Occasionally, you'll have to connect some of the clues you find, though these are mostly very obvious. There are also sporadic stealth-combat sections, but like the rest of the game, these offer no challenge at all.The presentation is also average. While the games looks very nice, the character design is uninspired and most character models are used over and over. The music is sparse, and while usually fitting the mood, it gets boring due to repetition. The story is uninteresting, has a lot of cliches and is mostly forgettable, though there are a couple of twists.This is not a bad game by any means and I can appreciate the hard work put into this. While I dislike writing bad reviews, with so many better options out there, it's hard to recommend this one."
