,Not Recommended,233290,17030107,"Posted: 13 July, 2015",all,Alex Demille,"I'm going to not recommend this game, primarily because it is just too short and has too many small issues with it; however, I do still think this is worth a play through.In Murdered: Soul Suspect, you play Ronin; a not-so-cleverly named man who is dead and searching for his killer. Through the game, you will help some random ghosts in what is I think some of the most interesting gameplay, and run around in crime scenes solving hide-and-seek puzzle games. The major flaw in this game comes with the very short play time and annoying time wasting monster encounters.Throughout the game you will have encounters with ""daemons"" who are your typical Metal Gear style pathed guards; they can only be killed from behind with a simple QTE and are more of a nusanse than actually being a challenge. By the end of the game, I went into the config and made it so they just didn't see me so I wouldn't have to fight them. It's not that fighting daemons is hard, it's just annoying and by the end of the game if you don't know where the escape rooms are you can just die if you screw up.The final encounter is lame and very confusing, I had to look up the solution. Again, like the daemons, this wasn't because it was hard, it was because the prompt wasn't clear on what I should do.The story has some decent writing in small parts. The noir monologue at the entrance to each game section is a neat touch. The two main characters are interesting, and there seems to be a decent about of background lore on Ronin (the PC). The collectables are interesting as they expand on the murder case and also include background about Salem (the town in which the game takes place). I have no idea if any of the lore is true, but it is nice they put it in. The hidden collectables are unique as they are just ghost/horror stories that have no connection to the main plot - its nice.Over all I think the game is worth a play through if you can pick it up for under $10. There is enough there to keep you entertained for an evening and if you like ghost stories than you should have a good time."
