76561197970532623,Recommended,233290,11542455,"Posted: 3 August, 2014",all,KnightErrant,"Interesting story.  It is like reading a book.  A bit short as I finished it in one afternoon.  No surprise clues at the end, you can figure out the mystery as the story progresses (which is a good thing).  I had guessed a few of the plot aspects before they happened, but I don't find that a negative.  It happens.The game concentrated on the story (which I liked) rather than combat with some story thrown in.  This may not appeal to some.The game is short.There were bad parts.  It was clear that the end was thrown together.  Not that the story didn't complete.  That was fine, but there were four major broken game development commandments.  Two appear right at the end.1.  You cannot save the game.  Ever.  It is a port to PC from a console.  There are automatic progress points.  The good thing is they do seem to happen often.2.  Flash sequences.  Some people like them, I don't.3.  Repeated cutscene (happens at end) when you fail (which will happen).  You can skip it after it starts, but forcing one to even go into it is bad.4.  Sudden timed sequence.  There is exactly one (two parts of one timed sequence) and none of the rest of the game has one.  It is short (the timed sequence), too.I'd recommend the game if you like to play a short story.  This is not a combat centered game.  It is a mystery and in that aspect it was fun to figure out the mystery.  Get it on sale.  Not worth a normal 50-60 dollar price tag.I'd like to see more products like this rather than the overdone shooters and what not, so I realise my suggestion to get it on sale isn't going to encourage more such development.I'm going to give it a yes but read the caveats in this article."
