76561198064155675,Recommended,233290,11939930,"Posted: 31 August, 2014",all,Dave,"Although this game is extremely buggy, it is a great game if you can get it to run. Your character is a detective who, as a ghost, spends the game trying to figure out the identity of a serial killer. There are a lot of CSI-style investigation scenes. Because your character is a ghost, he also uses supernatural abilities to solve the case. The game takes place in the town of Salem where the infamous witch trials took place. The graphics are stellar and you can view the area around your character in all directions as he explores Salem. Although most of the game is confined to investigations in limited areas that proceed in a somewhat linear fashion, you have some freedom to explore each area openly, and you must determine how to properly use your powers and wits to solve the case. The downside of this game is that the game did not start at all after I first downloaded it. SquareEnix support was no help. I went to CrashWiki (a website) and downloaded some dll files to my System32 folder in order to get this game to run. But the game did run after I downloaded the dlls. The game still crashed every now and then. There is also no support for the 32-bit version of Windows. You must have the 64-bit version of Windows for the game to run. I do have 64-bit Windows, but I still experienced some problems. You will not be able to run the game at all if you have 32-bit Windows."
