76561198149705160,Recommended,233290,13175403,"Posted: 30 November, 2014",all,Mhyrrlin,"Picked this one up on the Black Friday sale and I'm so glad I did. I've been wanting to play it but was put off by the high price tag.The controls feel a little strange, even though they're relatively typical for a PC game. I found the mouse movements to be incredibly sensitive, however, and wasn't able to find a way to easily slow it down. Once I got used to it, though, it was fine.  Don't expect super complex controls. Basically, you have forward, backwards, sideways and interact. Pay attention to what the screen tips are telling you about the type of interaction.The storyline is fascinating and if you like solving mysteries it will really pull you in. There are a few side mysteries to solve and ghost stories to find. The game doesn't send you running around all over the map for the mysteries, but it also isn't in your face about where you're supposed to be looking for clues. It's a nice balance. You get more shields (points) if you get the answer right the first time but you'll have second and third chances.The atmosphere is suitably spooky, the sound effects and background music is really creepy - especially with the lights out. Fighting demons is interesting and can be challenging.Overally, I'm really enjoying the game."
