76561198012222464,Recommended,233290,13727002,"Posted: 30 December, 2014",all,mfortunato,"Highly overlooked gem.  Just finished playing this and I thoroughly enjoyed it from beginning to end.  I do not understand why this game received such negative reviews. The story is entertaining and you're kept guessing until the end (although I had my suspicions - which turned out to be incorrect). The graphics are quite beautiful overall - the animations are very good.  The voice over work is very good - I really liked the main character. The gameplay on a computer keyboard is a tad clunky but I got used to it very quickly.  There is nothing that deterred me from being truly engaged in the story of Ronan, the main character - a detective who is murdered while trying to track a serial killer.NOTE: this is an adventure game.  In fact, I'd argue that it's almost an old-school adventure game wrapped up in a shiny, modern day package.  The goal of the game is to gather clues and solve puzzles.  There are a few moments that require stealth: when demons roam the area your character is traversing.  The demons look for ghosts and eat their essence (including Ronan's). But this is not an action game in any way - in fact, you can probably get through the whole game without ever having to fight one of the demons - simply run and hide from them (ok, not always so simply).Even searching for the hidden side quests is entertaining (something I still haven't finished - I'm about 83% of the way there as of my writing this). Scattered throughout the locations are hidden objects that need to be revealed and collected.  Once collecting all of them, you are treated to a ghost story - the history of that particular haunted object.  The ghost stories are well written and well voiced - I would have liked there to be some video or a slide show to go along with them instead of only audio, but I enjoyed them nonetheless.The game is quite inexpensive during Steam's seasonal sales and I highly recommend picking up a copy if you like a good detective story with some simple, but clever puzzle solving.  The game is engaging, the story is well-written, the characters beautifully rendered with excellent acting, and the sets are detailed and moody - perfect for a ghost story. I cannot say enough good things about this wonderful game."
