76561198013434430,Recommended,233290,16481856,"Posted: 17 June, 2015",all,eygam,"I got the game on sale and I think it was okay, but the full price is ridiculous. I like the game but it's not worth the full price and you should go through more reviews or gameplays even if it's on some 50 % off.I'd say most of the game is okay. And that's exactly the word. It's not great but it's not bad either. The general feeling when you finish the game will probably be something like... yeah, I had fun but it could (and should) have been much more fun.The story is fine but not breathtaking. It uses a lot of clichés but what really makes it dull is that there are too few characters. It's a detective story and you have like two possible suspects, not much mystery there.The detective part is... ehm. You collect clues and then you are supposed to draw some conclusion. Unfortunatelly, all you need to do is to click on the most obvious stuff you can and it's usualy the right answer. Sometimes, you even ""discover"" something you (as a player) must have thought before you started investigating because it's so flippin obvious.The stealth and fights with demons are really easy once you get a hang of it. Not much to say about it, the stealth parts could have been great but they ended up just dull. The demons are really creepy though, they look a bit as if they were dancing... but they wanna eat you... creepy.There are many collectibles. Some of them add to the story, which is great. Each area of the game has a ghost story which plays only if you find all related collectibles. These are great. Unfortunatelly, many collectibles just give you an achievement and that's is annoying. I also ended up with one or two collectibles missing in some catogories which brings me to...The saving system. It works fine, there are autosaves and even if you die, you dont lose much progress. But there is no way to make a hard save and once you reach a certain point in the game, you cannot enter most areas. So if you dont have all collectibles by the endgame, you will not get them unless you play again. And even then you'd have to go through almost the whole game because areas of the game open as you progress in the story.The few puzzles you encounter are really easy. You have some great mechanics (possessing people and cats, messing with electronics to make people move and get you through areas you cannot cross) but the creators really didnt use all the potential. I know puzzles weren't the point of the game but they could have add a lot of fun to the gameplay.I generally enjoyed the game, it's has a lot of genuine creepiness in it and it's mostly fun. But it gets repetitive even of it's a rather short game (I think I have like 12 hours with almost all collectibles, I think people do it faster) and you will be left with the feeling you expected more from it."
