76561198022227036,Recommended,233290,30519330,Posted: 14 March,all,rmp,"The game starts with your character being killed by a serial killer and you become a ghost needing to resolve your murder before he can 'move on'.  As you investigate the killer, you'll also help a girl that the killer is looking for (a medium who can see and hear ghosts).As a ghost, you get to do some neat tricks: pass through some walls, teleport short distances, possess people to read their minds, poltergeist objects. My favorite was possessing cats. It's too bad some of these weren't fleshed out a bit more, as they sound more interesting than they actually are in the game.The main danger to your character are demons that can kill you. You can kill the demons by sneaking up behind them and killing them with a keyboard and button click combo. You don't have much time to do it so the potential to screw it up is not high but still there. Mess it up and you're probably reloading. The threat is mostly when there are two demons in close proximity to each other. One will see you trying to sneak up on the other.When you investigate a scene, you get enough information that will lead you somewhere else. You go there, investigate, and that leads to your next destination again. Rinse and repeat. You can't get the investigations wrong and you'll keep looking for clues until the game says you've found enough. Even the dialogs with characters, you don't choose what to say, you only choose the order in which you'll say it. You can wander around the town and do a few side quests (helping other ghosts) but the town is not very big and there is not a whole lot to do other than travel to your next main objective. The progression is very linear. It would have made a good movie.Despite the shortcomings, I enjoyed the atmosphere and story. The mystery around the killer and the murders were great and had me hooked to the end."
