,Not Recommended,233290,11060646,"Posted: 3 July, 2014",all,Zardoz Xerxes,"Back hand clapping...I had to give up playing this today after the 30th time of trying to execute the same demon and forgetting that (unlike any other game) you have to hold the button down. For me this game is an endless cycle of: sneak up behind demon, press execute button, run away because ""I"" let them go (i.e. forgot to hold the button)...No option...Why for the love of god did they not include an auto hold on execute option in controls?! This awful command system is a game ruiner and all the hard work put into this game amounts to nothing because of it. It's very sad because I was enjoying the game. I have no problem sneaking up behind the demons but then in the heat of the moment I forget that it has a weirdly unique and bizarrely abnormal control system that has never been used in any other game.3rd Party software needed?The only way I could play this was if I used a program like xpadder to make the button toggle or hold for a time, but having to use 3rd party software to overcome a badly thought out and poorly implemented control system is ridiculous (for a 3rd person game, not a flight sim).No patch?If they make a patch I for this I might play it but since having an unplayable game taking up lots of space on my hdd is a stupid idea,  I will be uninstalling it and wont know if there is a patch because I am not going to bother checking (in much the same way they didn't bother putting an alternative to their useless command system)."
