,Recommended,233290,14452542,"Posted: 13 February, 2015",all,ビバップ,"Murdered: Soul Suspect was a good game.It wasn't here to be revolutionary, just a simple detective RPG.Graphics were not anything special, but they certainly weren't bad.Most of the setting was nice to look at for the most part.The atmosphere added a lot to the gameplay, although it would have been nice to see a change in scenery.The game was free roam to an extent, mainly in the main town which could get old very fast.The game was similar to the series made by telltale games, gameplay was obviously different, but a lot of aspects of the game seemed to take similar form.I enjoyed the plot, it wasn't particularly gamechanging but it was worth it for the unexpected ending.The ending was one that suddenly revealed an entire subplot that I wasn't entirely aware of until the end.Overall a decent game, the idea was good, it was a little rough around the edges, but it stayed consistent in gameplay and story.7/10Pros:Semi-free roam, not incredibly restrictive.Reminiscent of the Telltale game franchises.Plot is well developed, good backstory.Side-quests are fun little extras, each comes with a cutscene which is fun to watch.You can teleport and possess cats.Cons:Occasional lag during and after certain cutscenes. (i5, GTX 760)Combat is more of a chore than a challenge.Collectables are just out and about, only a portion are really hidden.Some parts of the gameplay that just make you say, ""What?""A lot of useless ghost remnants.Nitpicks:Voices were synced in close-up shots, desynced in distance shots.Teleporting was good when needed but a bit awkward in general.Cat possession could bug out sometimes.If you want to 100% this you should look at doing it in one run, you have to replay the whole game if you missanything.The objectives during certain quests weren't always the most obvious as they were in other parts of the game, and led to some sprinting around in circles searching for the last clues."
