,Recommended,233290,14376125,"Posted: 7 February, 2015",all,bademeistAr,"This is one of those games that would have sold a lot better if it wouldn't have been for the full 60 dollar price tag. Clocking in at around 5 hours of gameplay players are tasked to find their own killer as a ghost detective. The story is a nice mix of mystery, detective stories and a wink at Salem's well-known history. The gameplay consists of finding clues and piecing together hints (similar to LA Noire) as well as out of place stealth sections that quickly become repetative and unfortunately become more frequent near the end of the game. I however had fun playing Murdered Soul Suspect. It is exactly as long as it should be, the story doesn't go for an unneccessary ""DLC"" or ""Start of a Franchise"" Move (meaning, there is an actual ending to the story) and even on my sometimes a bit glitchy rig it ran smoothly on max without any problems.If you're interested and can pick it up on sale, go for it!"
